		<div id="welcome">

			<h4>*STAGE 1: CATEGORIES, TERMS, CONCEPTS AND SPECIFIC OBJECTS*</h4>
		 	<br />
		 	<div id="mobile-msg">Since the goal of Ybigh is to capture your unique mind, there's no good way to tell you how to use it. The best we can do is to suggest that, and sometimes, you may have to think creatively when considering how a category relates a given TCSO.</div>

			Each or any of the <i>terms, concept or specific objects</i> (<i>TCSO</i> for short) may invoke personal feelings, spark a particular philosophical interest, connect with you on spiritual level, all three or none at all. Based on your understanding of the <i>TCSO</i> [word] chosen, it’s up to you to reflect on your life’s experience and select the category, or categories, you feel best fit it.
			<br /><br />
			<ul class="about">
				<li>Dragging the mouse towards the dark corner suggests a <i>TCSO</i> that's more spiritual (has substance but is not relatable or is not understandable)</li>
				<li>Dragging the mouse towards the base color suggests a <i>TCSO</i> that's more material (is concrete and understandable or relatable)</li>
				<li>Dragging the mouse towards the lighter shade of color and the <i>TCSO</i> begins to take on both spiritual & material characteristics attaining parity at the pure white vertex.</li>
			</ul>
			<br />
			<img src="img/s1Img.jpg" style="float:left; margin:0 20px 15px 0;"/>
			<div>
				<strong><a href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#reminder">Select up to 4 categories</a> for any given <i>TCSO</i>:</strong><br /><br />
				<ul class="about">
					<li>Man's View of Himself/Herself (abbreviated to 'Himself')</li>
					<li>Man's Connections with Other than Himself</li>
					<li>Man's View of the World</li>
					<li>Man's Physical Activities</li>
				</ul>
				<strong>The word "Man" simply means the <i>universal man</i> of which you are an example. As such, you may:</strong><br /><br />
            	<ul class="about">
					<li>Personalize any or all <i>TCSO's</i> to yourself</li>
					<li>Think of others exclusively</li>
					<li>Think of yourself and others together</li>
            	</ul>
			</div>
			To make using Ybigh easier, we recommend reviewing the complete list of <i>TCSO's</i> [words] in Stage 1 before making your selections. Have fun. 
		</div>
